tasks.description:
Create new module hex-nexus/src/build_banner.rs containing ONE pure function:

```rust
/// Returns a one-line human-readable banner identifying this nexus build.
/// Used by `hex nexus status` and the dashboard header.
pub fn build_banner() -> String {
    format!("hex-nexus {}", env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION"))
}
```

Add ONE unit test that asserts the returned string starts with `hex-nexus ` (with trailing space).

Also add `pub mod build_banner;` to `hex-nexus/src/lib.rs` so cargo check sees the module. Place the `pub mod` declaration alphabetically among the existing top-level module declarations.

DO NOT modify any other files. DO NOT wire `build_banner()` into any caller — this is a pure addition. Cargo check is the gate; if it passes, the task is done.
